1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:13,000
AI agents can choose operational tools. But autonomy is not authority.
PALO-AI makes authority, policy, oversight and evidence visible.

2
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Pattern A: a Visual Governance Decision Gate normalizes each proposed action
and exposes Allowed, Approval Required and Denied outcomes.

3
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:39,000
The current visual gate is useful and testable, but advisory:
a workflow editor can still remove it.

4
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Pattern B: the Governed Executor keeps credentials behind PALO
and accepts only registered executors with schema-valid arguments.

5
00:00:52,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Policy runs outside the model. A one-time capability is consumed
before an allowlisted executor performs the action.

6
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Pattern C: human approval is bound to the digest
of one exact, immutable Action Claim.

7
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:31,000
The backend revalidates the same claim before secure resume.
Authenticated mobile delivery remains under development.

8
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Pattern D: Workflow Admission assesses workflow JSON, hosts,
destructive operations and missing governance coverage.

9
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Instance-level blocking and versioned workflow admission
are specified future capabilities, not current claims.

10
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:10,000
The installable alpha runs in n8n 2.30.7 with encrypted credentials
and three visible decision outputs.

11
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:23,000
It creates Action Claim 1.1, adds n8n execution metadata,
preserves immutable approval resume and fails closed.

12
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:36,000
In the live test, the authenticated PALO gateway denied
an action whose agent profile was deliberately missing.

13
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:49,000
n8n routed the decision to Denied with authorized set to false.
A successful denial is meaningful preview evidence.

14
00:02:49,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Developer preview: challenge the contracts with safe workflows.
n8n orchestrates. PALO governs whether it is authorized.
